fields.name: avg_family_size
fields.description: average family size in the village (for income tax purposes)

fields.name: bednet_infection_modifier
fields.description: effect of bednets on reducing infection

fields.name: chance_of_getting_the_flu
fields.description: % likelihood of getting the flu if no other diseases infect you

fields.name: child_2_effort
fields.description: effort coefficient for child between 5 and 10

fields.name: child_genders
fields.description: list of genders of the children in the order that they're born

fields.name: child_names
fields.description: names for the children in the order that they are born

fields.name: cotton_price
fields.description: price of cotton at the market

fields.name: cotton_productivity_exponent
fields.description: productivity coefficient for cotton production that assures decreasing marginal returns on farming effort (should be between 0.0 and 1.0)

fields.name: death_rate
fields.description: death rate of the villagers (natural causes)

fields.name: fertilizer_t1
fields.description: whether fertilizer was used 1 year ago

fields.name: fertilizer_t2
fields.description: whether fertilizer was used two years ago

fields.name: health
fields.description: health (%) of people in the family

fields.name: health_t1
fields.description: health of each family member 1 turn ago

fields.name: health_t3
fields.description: health of each family member 3 turns ago

fields.name: improvements
fields.description: what improvements the user is buying for the village this turn

fields.name: pregnant
fields.description: whether each person is pregnant or not

fields.name: sell_items
season
fields.description: what items the user is selling at the market this turn (item|quantity)

fields.name: sick
fields.description: whether each family member is sick

fields.name: death_threshold_1
fields.description: if a person's health drops below this threshold, they die immediately

fields.name: death_threshold_2
fields.description: if a person's average health for the last three turns is below this threshold they die

fields.name: doctor_visit_cost
fields.description: cost per person to visit a doctor

fields.name: drought_threshold
fields.description: mm of rainfall below which is considered a drought

fields.name: effort_too_high_health_loss
fields.description: number of health points lost per hour of effort above optimal.

fields.name: enable_free_bednets
fields.description: enable free bednet + canned epidemic event (free bednets only if epidemics are disabled)

fields.name: energy_req_scaling_factor
fields.description: set this to (1 / initial family size)

fields.name: free_bednet_year
fields.description: year of gameplay in which the free bednets + canned epidemic event happens

fields.name: fuelwood_health_loss
fields.description: health lost due to household use of fuel wood before the age of 5 (half this is lost thereafter)

fields.name: primary_school_effort
fields.description: hours/day per child that primary school takes up

fields.name: recovery_rate2
fields.description: added recovery coefficient if there is a clinic

fields.name: recovery_rate3
fields.description: added recovery coefficient if there is both a clinic and electricity

fields.name: resting_health_gain
fields.description: number of health points gained per hour of effort below optimal (ie, spent resting)

fields.name: road_subsidy_year
fields.description: year of gameplay after which a road subsidy becomes likely

fields.name: school_meals_calories
fields.description: how many calories are provided to each child in school if school meals are in place

fields.name: secondary_school_cost
fields.description: cost per turn per child in secondary school

fields.name: secondary_school_effort
fields.description: hours/day per child that secondary school takes up

fields.name: small_business_depreciation_rate
fields.description: depreciation rate of small business capital

fields.name: small_business_diminishing_return
fields.description: dimishing return effect for small business income

fields.name: small_business_drought_effect
fields.description: effect of drought on small business income

fields.name: small_business_electricity_effect
fields.description: effect of power grid on small business income

fields.name: small_business_epidemic_effect
fields.description: effect of epidemic on small business income

fields.name: small_business_productivity_effect
fields.description: effect of productivity and capital on small business income

fields.name: small_business_road_effect
fields.description: effect of road on small business income

fields.name: soil_depletion
fields.description: soil health when fertilizer hasn't been used in the last 3 years

fields.name: subsidy_price_reduction
fields.description: price of improvements (in % of original price) after NGO subsidization

fields.name: transport_cost_no_road
fields.description: cost to transport a ton of goods when there is no road

fields.name: transport_cost_road
fields.description: cost to transport a ton of goods when there is a road

fields.name: wood_price
fields.description: sale price per unit of wood

fields.name: ages
fields.description: ages of people in the family

fields.name: calculated_food_cost
fields.description: cost of food after other considerations

fields.name: crops
fields.description: what crops are planted in the fields

fields.name: died
fields.description: names of people who died this turn

fields.name: education
fields.description: number of turns of education each person has

fields.name: health_increment
fields.description: percentage that health improves each turn

fields.name: improvement_labels
fields.description: display labels for the village improvements

fields.name: improvement_prices
fields.description: purchase prices for each village improvement

fields.name: initial_infected_pop
fields.description: initially infected population (to jump-start the SIR model)

fields.name: maize_high_yield_seeds_multiplier
fields.description: multiplier - effect of high yield seeds on maize production

fields.name: maize_price
fields.description: price of maize at the market

fields.name: maize_productivity_exponent
fields.description: productivity coefficient for maize production that assures decreasing marginal returns on farming effort (should be between 0.0 and 1.0)

fields.name: market_items
fields.description: What items are available for purchase at the market

fields.name: market_items_labels
fields.description: display labels for items for sale in market

fields.name: market_purchase_prices
fields.description: purchase prices for each market item

fields.name: market_sell_prices
fields.description: sell prices of market items (0 = can't be resold)

fields.name: max_precipitation
fields.description: maximum precipitation for the region (mm).  anything less than 25% of this will be considered drought.

fields.name: microfinance_base_interest
fields.description: base interest rate for microfinance loans

fields.name: microfinance_drought_effect
fields.description: effect of drought on microfinance interest rate

fields.name: microfinance_epidemic_effect
fields.description: effect of epidemic on microfinance interest rate

fields.name: microfinance_repay_period
fields.description: number of turns to repay microfinance loan

fields.name: mortality2
fields.description: mortality rate multiplied by village health

fields.name: no_droughts_before
fields.description: year of gameplay before which there will be no droughts

fields.name: no_epidemics_before
fields.description: year of gameplay before which there will be no epidemics

fields.name: other_subsidy_year
fields.description: year of gameplay after which NGO subsidies may appear

fields.name: fertilizer_last_turn
fields.description: whether fertilizer was used in the last turn (needed because of turns vs years stuff)

fields.name: health_t2
fields.description: health of each family member 2 turns ago

fields.name: market
fields.description: whether the user went to the market this turn

fields.name: purchase_items
fields.description: what items the user is buying from the market this turn (item|quantity)

fields.name: schooling_state
fields.description: a list of the schooling state for each person

fields.name: subsidy_offers
fields.description: what village improvements have been offered to be subsidized by NGOs or the Government

fields.name: try_for_child
fields.description: try for a child this year

fields.name: user_messages
fields.description: a channel for the program to send status messages to the user interface.
